1
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:07,900
Mechanistic interpretability scores a component by the effect of ablating it in isolation.

2
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:11,600
But transformer circuits self-repair: remove a primary head and a dormant backup takes over.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:15,300
The primary now looks unimportant — the model repaired the damage — and so does the silent backup.

4
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:19,000
A first-order score is blind to both sides of the redundancy.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,700
CoAx asks a conditional question: once the primary set S is removed,

6
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:26,400
how much does each remaining unit's ablation effect grow?

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:30,100
A dormant backup has little effect alone but a large conditional effect — label-free and gradient-free.

8
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:33,800
The pairwise synergy is a whole matrix: the name-movers and their backups form a bright off-diagonal block.

9
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,500
That block is the self-repair module a per-head score cannot see.

10
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:41,200
Intact, the primaries write the answer; ablate them and the backups wake up and re-route to the logit.

11
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,900
On the GPT-2-small IOI circuit, CoAx lifts backup recovery from 0.33 to 0.91 ROC-AUC.

12
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:48,600
The documented backups move from the first-order blind spot to the top of the ranking — above every baseline.

13
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,300
Ablating the primaries barely moves the answer; only removing the backups too collapses it.

14
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:56,000
As the primaries are ablated, the backups grow in output norm and start writing the answer,

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,700
while matched random heads stay flat.

16
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:03,400
Freezing the backups to their dormant value removes 55% of the self-repair — the wake-up is causal.

17
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:07,100
The discovery is label-free and generalizes beyond IOI:

18
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,800
conditional completion transfers to the induction circuit across eight further models and six architecture families.

19
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:14,500
The recovered backups also repair the tools built on the same primitive:

20
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:18,200
attribution, capability knockout, and repair-aware pruning that wins at every scale from 124M to 7B.
